
TOPIC: MAP/COLOR4

712          02C8          COLOR4

The same as the above but for the
background (BAK) and border color.
Shadow for 53274 ($D01A). In GTIA mode
ten, 704 stores the background color
(BAK), while 712 becomes a normal
color register.

Here are the default (powerup) values
for the COLOR registers (PCOL
registers are all set to zero on
powerup):

Register    Color  =  Hue  Luminance
708 (CO.0)    40       2       8
709 (CO.1)   202      12      10
710 (CO.2)   148       9       4
711 (CO.3)    70       4       6
712 (CO.4)     0       0       0

--------------------------------------
Locations 713 to 735 ($2C9 to $2DF)
are spare bytes. Locations 736 to 767
($2E0 to $2FF) are for miscellaneous
use.

